OL,3,CNew legislation proposed to tackle
OL,4,Cviolence against women and girls in
OL,5,CJersey
OL,7,FResearch from the UK's Institute for
OL,8,FAddressing Strangulation argues that
OL,9,Fthere are several potential
OL,10,Fneurological effects from
OL,11,Fstrangulation, including significant
OL,12,Fbrain damage and the increased risk of
OL,13,Fsuffering from a stroke.
OL,15,FInitial analysis assumes that each
OL,16,Fcustodial sentence given for the
OL,17,Foffence would be five years, with
OL,18,Fprisoners serving approximately 3.3
OL,19,Fyears of this.
